snippet: Tiger Woods birdied two of his last three holes to salvage a par 72 in the wind and keep his two-shot lead over Zach Johnson in the World Challenge.
abstract: Tiger Woods takes third-round lead at Northwestern Mutual World Challenge; other golf results noted.
